@page "/privacy"
@using MudBlazor

<PageTitle>Privacy Policy - QSMPDLE</PageTitle>

<WebPage>

    <h2>
        Privacy Policy
    </h2>

    <p class="info">
        Last updated: June 2026
    </p>

    <MudAlert Severity="Severity.Success" Dense="true" Variant="Variant.Outlined" Class="mb-6">
        <strong>TL;DR:</strong> No accounts. No ads. QSMPDLE stores local progress in your browser and anonymous gameplay statistics on the server.
    </MudAlert>

    <section class="mb-5">
        <h3>
            The Very Short Version
        </h3>

        <p>
            QSMPDLE does not ask for personal information.
        </p>

        <p>
            No accounts.<br />
            No sign-ups.<br />
            No advertising trackers.<br />
            No ads.
        </p>

        <p>
            The app does generate a random player id in your browser so daily streaks,
            game restoration, and statistics can work. That id is not connected to a
            name, email address, account, or login.
        </p>

        <p>
            Some gameplay events are sent to the server so global and per-player game
            statistics can be calculated reliably.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-5">
        <h3>
            What Does QSMPDLE Store?
        </h3>

        <p>
            QSMPDLE stores a small amount of information in your browser so the game can
            restore progress between visits:
        </p>

        <ul>
            <li>current daily, archive, or practice game state;</li>
            <li>guesses already made in an unfinished game;</li>
            <li>whether the win/loss popup was already seen;</li>
            <li>a random player id;</li>
            <li>daily statistics such as played games, wins, streaks, and guess distribution.</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="mt-3">
            If you clear your browser data, QSMPDLE loses this local state too.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-5">
        <h3>
            What Does The Server Know?
        </h3>

        <p>
            The server receives normal technical requests needed to display the website.
            It also stores anonymous gameplay records used for statistics and game reliability.
        </p>

        <p>
            Stored gameplay records may include:
        </p>

        <ul>
            <li>the random player id generated in your browser;</li>
            <li>a random game id;</li>
            <li>game mode, daily number, and target character id;</li>
            <li>guess character ids and guess order;</li>
            <li>game start and finish timestamps;</li>
            <li>whether the game was won and how many guesses it took.</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="mt-3">
            QSMPDLE does not store account profiles, names, email addresses, passwords,
            or payment information, because the app does not ask for them.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-5">
        <h3>
            Why Store Gameplay Statistics?
        </h3>

        <p>
            Statistics are stored so the app can count games played and won exactly once,
            calculate streaks and guess distributions, show practice stats, and build
            aggregate global stats.
        </p>

        <p>
            These records are intentionally minimal and gameplay-focused.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-5">
        <h3>
            Cookies
        </h3>

        <p>
            QSMPDLE uses browser storage for essential game state and player statistics.
            The app may also use essential cookies or framework storage required for the
            site to function correctly.
        </p>

        <p>
            No advertising cookies.
            No tracking cookies.
            No "follow you around the internet for six months" cookies.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-5">
        <h3>
            Third-Party Services
        </h3>

        <p>
            To stay online, QSMPDLE may rely on infrastructure providers such as:
        </p>

        <ul>
            <li>Railway</li>
            <li>Cloudflare</li>
        </ul>

        <p>
            These services may process technical information necessary to deliver
            and secure the website.
        </p>

        <p>
            If you choose to share results, QSMPDLE may open a share target such as X,
            Telegram, or Reddit with the share text you selected. Those services are
            separate from QSMPDLE and are governed by their own policies.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-5">
        <h3>
            Security
        </h3>

        <p>
            Reasonable efforts are made to keep the website secure.
        </p>

        <p>
            No website can guarantee perfect security.
            You can be sure that if somebody invents perfectly secure software, they'll quickly become very rich.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-5">
        <h3>
            Contact
        </h3>

        <p>
            Questions, bug reports, suggestions, or complaints that today's answer
            should obviously have been someone else can be submitted through the
            project's GitHub repository.
        </p>
    </section>

</WebPage>

<style>
    .privacy-card p {
        line-height: 1.8;
        opacity: 0.95;
    }

    .story-box {
        padding: 2rem;
        border-radius: .75rem;
        background: var(--panel);
        border: .125rem solid var(--panel-edge);
        box-shadow: inset 0 0 0 .0625rem var(--black);
    }

    .story-box p:last-child {
        margin-bottom: 0;
    }
</style>
